  "texts": [
    "In LMA3 [94], the agent can autonomously set goals for itself, and gradually improve its capability by exploring the environment and receiving feedback from a reward function.",
    "Following this mechanism, the agent can acquire knowledge and develop capabilities according to its own preferences.",
    "In SALLM-MS [95], by integrating advanced large language models like GPT-4 into a multi-agent system, agents can adapt and perform complex tasks, showcasing advanced communication capabilities, thereby realizing self-driven evolution in their interactions with the environment.",
    "In CLMTWA [96], by using a large language model as a teacher and a weaker language model as a student, the teacher can generate and communicate natural language explanations to improve the student's reasoning skills via theory of mind.",
    "The teacher can also personalize its explanations for the student and intervene only when necessary, based on the expected utility of intervention."
  ],
